<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-09-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-09-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="900" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d900">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 891.001.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Shah of Persia</gloss> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">President of the United
                            States</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-09-30"><hi rend="italic">September 30,
                                    1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I beg you, Mr. President, to accept my earnest thanks for the condolence
                            you were so good as to send me on the occasion of the death of the
                            Regent Azedolmolk.</p>
                        <p>In the name of His Majesty the Shah:</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Mostofiolmemalek</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">President of Council.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>